headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Royal Caribbean Cruises (RCL) After A 308% Five-Year Run?
summary: If you are wondering whether Royal Caribbean Cruises is still reasonably priced after a strong run, the starting point is to understand what the current market expects and how that lines up with its fundamentals. The stock last closed at US$304.33, with returns of 9.1% over 7 days, 22.6% over 30 days, 7.4% year to date and 35.7% over 1 year, plus a very large 3 year gain that is close to 4x and a 5 year return of 308.3%. These moves have kept Royal Caribbean in focus as investors weigh how...
